    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.11m"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">11m</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">PUBLIC LIBRARY
                        <lb/>
                    EAST ST. LOUIS, ILLINOIS</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 7, 1953</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Professor of English,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>College of Liberal Arts,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Jesse Hall,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>After being out of school for three years, since I graduated in February, 1950, I look back on my association with you in your class in Epic America with warmest remembrances.</p>
                
                <p>It has been an inspiration to me since then and I regard our brief association together as one looks on a relation of a dear friend.</p>
                
                <p>I am planning to visit Columbia during the annual Journalism Week in April at which time I want to see you again and tell you I do remember you and your kindness to me.</p>
                
                <p>My copy of the "Cycle of the West" always has something new to be discovered and like an ever-flowing spring of cool water it refreshes my mind and heart to live again with those heroes of the last frontier.</p>
                
                <p>And so until we meet again, my warmest remembrances to you and Mrs. Neihardt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Thomas W. Wright</signed>
                    <signed>Thomas W. Wright,
                    assistant librarian</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
